aspace_helpers.title: we need to import a straggler EAD (C1609)

comments.body:
This is the transformation workflow from the days of the migration (SVN readme):

1. Create container entities from dsc2 and classic containers: 
svn://lib-svn.princeton.edu/libsvn/trunk/rbscXSL/ASpace tools/get-containers.xquery
svn://lib-svn.princeton.edu/libsvn/trunk/rbscXSL/ASpace tools/classic_2_dsc2_containers.xq

2. Transform EADs: 
svn://lib-svn.princeton.edu/libsvn/trunk/rbscXSL/ASpace tools/ASpace_do_containers.xq
svn://lib-svn.princeton.edu/libsvn/trunk/rbscXSL/ASpace tools/ASpace_do_cleanup.xq

3. MUST run after EAD transformation: Extract Agents names_A-F and names_G-Z with get-agent-info-and-delete.xq and delete names, bioghists from EAD;
Remove empty elements with remove-empty-agent-wrappers.xq

4. Create CSV from names_A-F, names_G-Z using names2csv.xq 

5. Validate: svn://lib-svn.princeton.edu/libsvn/trunk/rbscXSL/ASpace tools/validate.xquery (5 min), 
svn://lib-svn.princeton.edu/libsvn/trunk/rbscXSL/ASpace tools/validate-containers.xquery
This is urgent: per Kelly, Dan and Alexis are hoping this can be done this week.

bibdata.title: Host holdings should be grouped by the host record mms id that they are attached to.

comments.body: The `Alma::AvailabilityResponse` that we use from the alma_rb gem will merge in the constituent record all the host holdings with no indicator if these holdings are from another host mms_id. I'm looking into what would be the best way to identify this;
I'm going to try a reindex before looking into it more closely
Reindexing doesn't fix it. @kelea99 do you think you could help me understand the impact of this issue?
Actually reindexing made the error change. I'm linking the new honeybadger error in the description.

When attempting to undertake the upgrade during the maintenance window, the following error arose:

![image.png](https://images.zenhubusercontent.com/5b5b6aed981c3204c9ed06c8/ff007a3a-eb8d-43c3-b6ed-ca328bfc73b5)

A Symplectic Support ticket which is currently tracking this is https://support.symplectic.co.uk/support/tickets/354904.

openpublishing.title: OJS Health Science Theme Does not Work

comments.body: The Health Science theme should look like this  https://demo.publicknowledgeproject.org/ojs3/demo/index.php/health-sciences. The journal title and homepage image are customizable in the OJS (which I already did). The layout/display should be the same with the above demo site.

This looks like it is a local caching issue for the reporting user's browser. Visiting https://ojs-staging.princeton.edu/index.php/tj1 in a private tab shows the following: This is the Health Sciences theme minus the configurations in the above example.

Closing this issue; the theme is configured and displaying appropriately according to the user.  There is an additional issue reported for custom header images not uploading.  I am coordinating a meeting with the stakeholder to review this and open tickets together if needed.
